Context: Im trying to build fancy, client oriented and viral landing page for my SaaS.
Main Idea of the SaaS: My SaaS is an automated social media content publishing platform that runs on autopilot for small businesses and creators. Customers purchase a subscription plan (e.g., "1 Facebook post per week"), complete a simple onboarding questionnaire about their brand and preferences, and authorize their social media accounts via OAuth. The system then automatically generates and publishes content on their behalf based on their brand voice and inputs, requiring zero ongoing effort from the customer. The entire workflow—from payment to content creation to scheduled publishing—is fully automated using no-code tools. Each customer is completely isolated in a secure multi-tenant architecture, allowing the platform to scale to hundreds of users simultaneously.
Main purpose of landing page: convince visitors to sign up bu clickeing a button which will redirect them to another website

Steps you need to follow:
1. Create a git repository with name "MetaPilot" and add ONLY necessary file. Do not forget to use .gitignore file and put there files according to best practices
2. Create Landing Page using @frontend_design skill. You can inspire by:
- [https://www.jasper.ai/](https://www.jasper.ai/)
